page.title: 15CHILDRENS VEIW STUBHAMPTON
page.content: When we went to Stubhampton Bottom we walked through two areas,Well Bottom and Washers Pit. We saw lots of flowers,trees,wild plants,insects and birds.We also saw some squirrels and rabbits.In Washers Pit we saw clear tracks of deer prints and fox prints but we did not see the actual animals. We saw some Oak trees,Hazel trees, Beech trees,Deadly Nightshade and Broom.There were birds happily singing in the trees and bushes,flying from bough to bough.In Washers Pit the trees look so nice surrounded by green plants and colourful flowers.At Well Bottom the trees were overgrown in places and it was difficult to walk. In a clearing there was a wooden look-out tower for seeing fires.
